To show a little information about a post in the user's profile when they click on "Забронировать", you can modify the "bookMK" function in the "SignUpForMK" component to add the booked post data to the user's profile in Firebase, instead of just navigating to the "Profile" screen.

For example, you can modify the "bookMK" function as follows:

```
const bookMK = () => {
  const currentUserID = firebase.auth().currentUser.uid;
  const bookedMKData = {
    name: mkData.name,
    time: mkData.time.toDate().toISOString(),
    image: mkData.image,
    price: mkData.price
  };
  firebase
    .database()
    .ref(`users/${currentUserID}/bookedMK`)
    .push(bookedMKData)
    .then(() => {
      // Show a little information about the booked post in the user's profile
      navigation.navigate('Profile', { bookedMKData });
    });
};
```

In this updated implementation, we pass the "bookedMKData" object to the "Profile" screen as a route parameter, so that we can display it in the user's profile.

Now, in the "Profile" component, you can access the booked post data from the route parameters and show it in the UI. For example, you can modify the "ProfilePaidMK" section as follows:

```
